<infoparam name="UML Note" value="Incoherencies:

1. The block diagram lists &apos;EmergencyMessage&apos; and &apos;WarningMessage&apos; as separate entities, 
    which is inconsistent as the system specification suggests they are the same.
 -&gt; OK

2. The &apos;Car&apos; block does not include attributes for vehicle dynamic status details like speed, acceleration, 
    and heading which are mentioned to be part of the information sent in warning messages according to the system specification.
 -&gt; OK (Warning message include these informations)

3. The &apos;CommunicationUnit&apos; block should explicitly signal sending information about the vehicle dynamic status 
    and the detailed information about the planned actions to the DSRCInterface, as per the system specification.
 -&gt; Partial (dangerAssessed, warning message)

4. There is no representation of the &apos;Chassis Domain Bus&apos; as a mediator for information flow between ECU, 
Chassis Safety Controller, and other components, which is crucial according to the system specification.
 -&gt; Partial (block added, but simply connected to ECU)

5. Neither diagram provides a clear representation of the association between the detected danger, the assessment process 
    by the Chassis Safety Controller, and the subsequent action taken which is a critical part of the system specification.
 -&gt; OK

6. The system specification mentions nearby vehicles reacting to the warning message, but neither diagram specifies 
    the receiver&apos;s actions upon receiving the warning message, such as how the other vehicles process or react to the information.
 -&gt; KO
